    <!-- EXECUTIVE SUMMARY SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="executive-summary" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Executive Summary</h2>
            
            <div class="row" style="margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <div class="col-50" style="background-color: #ffebee; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-left: 4px solid #d32f2f; border-radius: 4px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #d32f2f; margin-top: 0;">🔴 Current State: FRAGMENTED</h3>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                        <li>Multiple credential storage methods (db_config.json, env vars, encrypted files, hardcoded)</li>
                        <li>No unified credential management interface</li>
                        <li>Insecure plaintext storage in docker-compose files</li>
                        <li>Inconsistent handling across dev/test/prod environments</li>
                        <li>db_config.json intentionally untracked in git (per-machine authority - solved)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-50" style="background-color: #e8f5e9; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-left: 4px solid #388e3c; border-radius: 4px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #388e3c; margin-top: 0;">🟢 Target State: UNIFIED</h3>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                        <li>Single admin interface for all credentials (database, APIs, secrets)</li>
                        <li>Environment-aware credential handling (dev, Docker, K8s)</li>
                        <li>Encrypted at-rest storage with key rotation</li>
                        <li>Audit logging for all credential access</li>
                        <li>Interactive setup via <code>/diagnostic/setup/debug</code> (app starts even if misconfigured)</li>
                        <li><strong>Keep db_config.json as foundation</strong> until all other credentials safely in database</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: #f3e5f5; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-left: 4px solid #7b1fa2; border-radius: 4px;">
                <h3 style="color: #7b1fa2; margin-top: 0;">🔑 Critical Architecture Decision</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                    <strong>db_config.json is the chicken-egg solution:</strong> Each computer maintains its own copy (not tracked in git). This solves the bootstrap problem - we need credentials to load credentials from a database. Database credentials are the foundation; once safely accessible, all other credentials (Proxmox, Cloudflare, Groq, Redis) can move into encrypted database storage.
                </p>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CURRENT AUDIT SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="current-audit" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">2. Current Credentials Audit</h2>

            <h3 id="audit-database" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">2.1 Database Credentials</h3>

            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Location</th>
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Storage Method</th>
                    <th style="text-align: center; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Security</th>
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Used By</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>db_config.json</code></td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">JSON file</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">❌ Plaintext</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Comserv.pm:_initialize_database_config()</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>docker-compose.dev.yml</code></td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Environment variables</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">❌ Plaintext</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Dev container (port 3000)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>docker-compose.prod.yml</code></td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Environment variables (manual setup)</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">⚠️ Requires manual setup</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Prod container (port 5000)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>.env.local</code> (proposed)</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Environment file (gitignored)</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: #388e3c; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Secure (local only)</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Native dev (port 3001)</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-medium);"><strong>Assessment:</strong> Works for dev/test but production credentials exposed in plaintext. No encryption mechanism (unlike Proxmox). Different implementations for each environment.</p>

            <h3 id="audit-git-status" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">2.1a Credential Audit Results (A.3 - Dec 26, 2025)</h3>
            
            <div style="background-color: #e8f5e9; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-left: 4px solid #388e3c; border-radius: 4px;">
                <h4 style="color: #388e3c; margin-top: 0;">✅ Audit Findings VERIFIED & IMPLEMENTED (Jan 13, 2026)</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                    <strong>Dec 26 findings:</strong> docker-compose.dev.yml had hardcoded password issue. <strong>Current status (Jan 13):</strong> ALL FIXED. docker-compose.dev.yml and docker-compose.prod.yml now use environment variable references (${COMSERV_DB_*}) for K8s Secrets pattern compatibility. .env files properly gitignored. Audit completed and verified.
                </p>
            </div>

            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">File</th>
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Status</th>
                    <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Details</th>
                    <th style="text-align: center; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Action</th>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: #ffebee;">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>docker-compose.dev.yml</code></td>
                    <td style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">🔴 CRITICAL</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Lines 18, 23: Hardcoded password <code>UA=nPF8*m+T#</code> in GIT for dev env. Tracked in git - exposed to anyone with repo access.</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ FIXED - Use env var refs</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>.env</code> (root)</td>
                    <td style="color: #388e3c; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ SECURE</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">GITIGNORED (not tracked in git). Local machine only. Contains real passwords but never committed.</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ OK</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>.env.development</code></td>
                    <td style="color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">⚠️ MIXED</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">TRACKED in git (committed). Contains placeholder <code>dev_password_change_me</code> - not a real password. Safe for dev but demonstrates pattern.</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ OK</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>docker-compose.prod.yml</code></td>
                    <td style="color: #388e3c; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ SECURE</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Uses env var references: <code>${COMSERV_DB_PRODUCTION_SERVER_PASSWORD}</code>. No hardcoded values. Requires external setup.</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ OK</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>docker-compose.staging.yml</code></td>
                    <td style="color: #388e3c; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ SECURE</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Uses env var references: <code>${DB_PASS_STAGING}</code>. No hardcoded values. Requires external setup.</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ OK</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><code>db_config.json</code></td>
                    <td style="color: #388e3c; font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ SECURE</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">GITIGNORED. Per-machine configuration. Each developer maintains their own copy.</td>
                    <td style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ OK</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Conclusion</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>Single Issue Found:</strong> <code>docker-compose.dev.yml</code> contains hardcoded passwords in GIT. This is low-risk (dev environment) but violates security best practices. <strong>Fix:</strong> Replace hardcoded values with environment variable references matching prod/staging pattern. When running locally, users will load credentials from local <code>.env</code> file (gitignored).
            </p>

            <h3 id="audit-api" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">2.2 API Credentials</h3>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Proxmox (VM Management)</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Storage:</strong> <code>config/proxmox_credentials.json</code> (AES-256 encrypted)</li>
                <li><strong>Encryption Key:</strong> <code>PROXMOX_ENCRYPTION_KEY</code> env var or <code>.proxmox_encryption_key</code> file</li>
                <li><strong>Module:</strong> <code>Comserv::Util::ProxmoxCredentials</code></li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Best practice (encrypted at rest + env var override)</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Ollama (LLM Integration)</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Hardcoded host <code>localhost:11434</code> (no auth required)</li>
                <li><strong>Module:</strong> <code>Comserv::Model::Ollama</code></li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Appropriate for local-only, would need enhancement for remote API</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Cloudflare (DNS Management)</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Not yet implemented</li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> 🔴 Would need AES-256 encryption and admin UI to manage</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Groq (x.ai LLM Integration)</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Not yet implemented - Future work for AI integration</li>
                <li><strong>Required:</strong> API key from x.ai</li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> 🔴 Awaiting credentials; will need AES-256 encryption and admin UI</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="audit-redis" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">2.3 Redis Credentials</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Default Password:</strong> <code>redispass_dev</code> hardcoded in <code>docker-compose.yml</code></li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ⚠️ Default in code, no rotation mechanism</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- UNIFIED MANAGEMENT PLAN SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="management-plan" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3. Unified Credential Management Plan</h2>

            <h3 id="phase-0" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 0: Remove Blocking MySQL Container (COMPLETED 2025-12-21)</h3>

            <div style="background-color: #e8f5e9; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-left: 4px solid #388e3c; border-radius: 4px;">
                <h4 style="color: #388e3c; margin-top: 0;">✅ Completed Actions</h4>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                    <li><strong>Removed config-db MySQL container</strong> from /docker-compose.yml (was blocking web services)</li>
                    <li><strong>Removed config-db dependency</strong> from web-dev and web-prod services (lines 101-104, 152-155)</li>
                    <li><strong>Removed config_db_data volume</strong> from volumes section</li>
                    <li><strong>Deleted blib/ artifacts</strong>: Removed duplicated docker-compose files from Comserv/blib/lib/Comserv/</li>
                    <li><strong>Updated comments</strong> in docker-compose.yml to reflect removal of config-db reference</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: #fff9c4; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-left: 4px solid #fbc02d; border-radius: 4px;">
                <h4 style="color: #f57f17; margin-top: 0;">📋 Why This Removes the Blockage</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                    The config-db MySQL container was preventing web-dev and web-prod from starting due to <code>depends_on: condition: service_healthy</code>. If config-db failed to start or became unhealthy, the entire application stack would fail. Since database credentials are managed via db_config.json and environment variables (COMSERV_DB_* pattern), the local MySQL container was not necessary. Removing it eliminates a single point of failure.
                </p>
            </div>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-medium);"><strong>Status Update (2025-12-21 18:45 UTC):</strong> Container started successfully with supervisor running and attempting to launch Catalyst. Supervisor and redis are healthy. New issue detected: Catalyst application exits with code 2 on startup (separate from config-db removal - appears to be application-level startup error in comserv-server.psgi or Perl module loading).</p>
            
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-medium);"><strong>Next Session:</strong> Debug Catalyst startup error (examine catalyst_error.log for Perl/module errors). Config-db blocker is REMOVED and no longer preventing container initialization.</p>

            <h3 id="phase-1" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 1: Interactive Setup via Diagnostics Interface (Weeks 1-3)</h3>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Deliverables:</strong></p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Diagnostic Setup Page:</strong> <code>/diagnostic/setup/debug</code> - Interactive first-run wizard integrated into diagnostic interface</li>
                <li><strong>Key Feature:</strong> Application must START EVEN IF MISCONFIGURED - guides user through errors as they encounter them</li>
                <li><strong>Database Credentials Panel:</strong> Edit host, port, username, password with test connection button</li>
                <li><strong>API Credentials Panel:</strong> Add/edit/delete for Proxmox, Cloudflare, Groq, future APIs</li>
                <li><strong>Secrets Manager Panel:</strong> Generate/rotate Redis password, view all secrets</li>
                <li><strong>Git Integration:</strong> Leverage existing git pull capability for config management</li>
            </ul>

            <div style="background-color: #fff9c4; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-left: 4px solid #fbc02d; border-radius: 4px;">
                <h4 style="color: #f57f17; margin-top: 0;">⚠️ Why Not /setup/credentials Wizard?</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                    Previous attempts at standalone setup wizards failed because they try to prevent app startup. Instead, the application starts normally (using db_config.json fallback or environment variables), then guides the user through <code>/diagnostic/setup/debug</code> when configuration is incomplete. This ensures the app is always accessible, even during initial setup.
                </p>
            </div>

            <h3 id="phase-2" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 2: Unified Encrypted Storage (Weeks 2-4)</h3>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Approach: Encrypted Files (External Config, Not Comserv.pm)</strong></p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Store in <code>Comserv/config/credentials/</code> (gitignored)</li>
                <li>Use AES-256 encryption (reuse ProxmoxCredentials pattern)</li>
                <li>Separate files: <code>database_ency.enc</code>, <code>database_forager.enc</code>, <code>api_proxmox.enc</code>, <code>api_cloudflare.enc</code>, <code>api_groq.enc</code></li>
                <li><strong>⚠️ DO NOT store settings in Comserv.pm:</strong> Comserv.pm is difficult to debug if broken; prefer external configuration files</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="phase-3" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 3: Environment-Specific Loading (Weeks 3-5)</h3>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Priority Order for Credential Sources:</strong></p>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Environment variables (<code>COMSERV_DB_HOST</code>, etc.)</li>
                <li>Docker secrets (<code>/run/secrets/db_pass</code>)</li>
                <li>Kubernetes secrets (<code>/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/db/</code>)</li>
                <li>Encrypted files (<code>Comserv/config/credentials/</code>)</li>
                <li>db_config.json (legacy fallback)</li>
            </ol>

            <h3 id="phase-4" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 4: Application Code Changes (Weeks 4-6)</h3>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>New Module:</strong> <code>Comserv/Util/CredentialsManager.pm</code></p>
            <pre style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto;"><code style="color: var(--text-color);">sub get_database_credentials {
    my ($self, $database_name) = @_;
    # Priority: env vars → docker secrets → k8s secrets → encrypted files → db_config.json
}

sub get_api_credentials {
    my ($self, $api_name) = @_;
    # Same pattern for all API credentials
}</code></pre>

            <h3 id="phase-5" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 5: Testing & Audit (Weeks 7-8)</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Unit tests for CredentialsManager</li>
                <li>Integration tests: dev → docker dev → docker prod → K8s</li>
                <li>Security audit: verify no plaintext credentials logged</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="phase-6" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 6: Production Rollout & Gradual Migration (Week 9+)</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Migrate existing credentials to encrypted format</li>
                <li>Enable new CredentialsManager by default</li>
                <li><strong>KEEP db_config.json as fallback</strong> - it remains the foundation and emergency recovery mechanism</li>
                <li>Once all other credentials safely in database, then discuss deprecation</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- EXISTING ASSETS SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="existing-assets" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3A. Existing Credential Infrastructure (Assets to Consolidate)</h2>
            
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Critical Discovery:</strong> DO NOT recreate existing functionality. These modules exist and can be refactored into unified framework:</p>

            <h3 id="asset-utilities" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">✅ Existing Utility Modules</h3>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Comserv::Util::ProxmoxCredentials (AES-256 Encryption Pattern)</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/ProxmoxCredentials.pm</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> AES-256 encryption/decryption for API credentials</li>
                <li><strong>Key Features:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Encrypted at-rest storage in <code>config/proxmox_credentials.json</code></li>
                        <li>Encryption key management (<code>.proxmox_encryption_key</code> file or env var)</li>
                        <li>Uses Crypt::CBC + Crypt::OpenSSL::AES (industry standard)</li>
                        <li>Logging integration via Comserv::Util::Logging</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Proven, production-ready</li>
                <li><strong>Refactoring Plan:</strong> Extract encryption/decryption logic into <code>Comserv::Util::Encryption</code> module that ProxmoxCredentials and new CredentialsManager can both use</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">2. Comserv::Util::EnvFileManager</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/EnvFileManager.pm</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Read/write .env files with backup capability</li>
                <li><strong>Key Features:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Parse .env files (handles quoted values, special chars)</li>
                        <li>Automatic backup before writes</li>
                        <li>Secret detection (identifies password/key/token vars)</li>
                        <li>Used by import_env_to_db.pl</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Complete, refactor-ready</li>
                <li><strong>Refactoring Plan:</strong> Keep as-is; integrate with CredentialsManager to load env vars as source</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3. Comserv::Util::RemoteDB</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/RemoteDB.pm</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Execute queries on remote databases using stored connections</li>
                <li><strong>Key Features:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Query execution (SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE)</li>
                        <li>Integration with <code>Comserv::Model::RemoteDB</code></li>
                        <li>Connection validation</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Functional (used by RemoteDB Model)</li>
                <li><strong>Refactoring Plan:</strong> Keep as-is; will use CredentialsManager to get connection details</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4. Comserv::Util::ConfigDatabaseInit</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Util/ConfigDatabaseInit.pm</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Initialize separate "config database" and import DBI credentials</li>
                <li><strong>Key Features:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Creates <code>database_connections</code> table in config DB</li>
                        <li>Auto-imports from <code>dbi_config.json</code> if exists</li>
                        <li>Used during app startup (currently DISABLED in Comserv.pm to prevent segfaults)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ⚠️ Partially broken (segfault issues) - see Comserv.pm line 214-217</li>
                <li><strong>Refactoring Plan:</strong> Do NOT use separate config DB. Instead, store credentials in primary ency database in new <code>ApplicationCredentials</code> table. ConfigDatabaseInit was overengineering solution.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="asset-scripts" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">✅ Existing Scripts (Can be Refactored)</h3>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. migrate_proxmox_credentials.pl</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/script/migrate_proxmox_credentials.pl</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Migrate proxmox creds from legacy format to AES-256</li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Working example of encryption migration</li>
                <li><strong>Refactoring Plan:</strong> Pattern can be reused for <code>migrate_database_credentials.pl</code> - similar approach but for ency/forager DB creds</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">2. import_env_to_db.pl</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/script/import_env_to_db.pl</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Import all .env variables to <code>EnvVariable</code> database table</li>
                <li><strong>Key Features:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Reads .env file using EnvFileManager</li>
                        <li>Auto-detects secrets vs regular vars</li>
                        <li>Stores in <code>EnvVariable</code> result class with <code>is_secret</code> flag</li>
                        <li>Dry-run mode to preview before applying</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Complete, currently uses EnvVariable table</li>
                <li><strong>Refactoring Plan:</strong> Keep for env var import; will also create similar <code>import_db_credentials.pl</code> for specialized handling of COMSERV_DB_* vars</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3. test_remotedb_logic.pl</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/script/test_remotedb_logic.pl</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Test remote database connection logic</li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Diagnostic tool</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="asset-database-tables" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">✅ Existing Database Tables</h3>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. EnvVariable (ency database)</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/EnvVariable.pm</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Stores environment variables in database</li>
                <li><strong>Key Fields:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><code>key</code> - Variable name</li>
                        <li><code>value</code> - Variable value (stored plaintext - OK for non-secrets)</li>
                        <li><code>var_type</code> - Type (string, int, boolean, json)</li>
                        <li><code>is_secret</code> - Boolean flag (1 if secret, 0 if not)</li>
                        <li><code>is_editable</code> - Whether admin can edit</li>
                        <li><code>editable_by_roles</code> - JSON array of roles</li>
                        <li><code>description</code> - Human description</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Table exists and has audit table (EnvVariableAuditLog)</li>
                <li><strong>Refactoring Plan:</strong> Can be extended for database credentials (add is_database_credential flag), but better to create separate <code>ApplicationCredentials</code> table for clarity</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">2. EnvVariableAuditLog</h4>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/EnvVariableAuditLog.pm</code></li>
                <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Audit trail for environment variable changes</li>
                <li><strong>Status:</strong> ✅ Exists (pattern to reuse for credential auditing)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="asset-consolidation" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">📋 Consolidation Strategy for Phase 1</h3>

            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
