            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CONTAINERIZATION CONSIDERATIONS -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="containerization" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4A. Containerization & Pre-Configured Deployment</h2>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>Important:</strong> Containers may be pulled from Git or Docker Hub as pre-built images. This changes the credential injection workflow.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Credential Injection for Containerized Deployments</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Development Containers (docker-compose.dev.yml):</strong> Credentials via environment variables (acceptable for dev)</li>
                <li><strong>Production Containers (docker-compose.prod.yml):</strong> Use Docker secrets or K8s secrets, NOT hardcoded env vars</li>
                <li><strong>Pre-configured Images:</strong> Image itself must NOT contain credentials; configuration injected at runtime</li>
                <li><strong>Git Pull Integration:</strong> Leverage existing git pull capability in <code>/diagnostic/setup/debug</code> for initial configuration</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Database Migration Path for Pre-Configured Containers</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Container Startup:</strong> Reads db_config.json or environment variables (db_config.json loaded from mounted volume)</li>
                <li><strong>First Access:</strong> If /diagnostic/setup/debug is visited, user can verify/update credentials</li>
                <li><strong>Encrypted Storage:</strong> Once CredentialsManager is ready, migrate to encrypted files mounted as volumes</li>
                <li><strong>Database Storage:</strong> Final stage: credentials stored in database, retrieved via CredentialsManager</li>
            </ol>

            <div style="background-color: #e8f5e9; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-left: 4px solid #388e3c; border-radius: 4px;">
                <h4 style="color: #388e3c; margin-top: 0;">✅ Current Verification Status</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                    See <a href="/diagnostic/docker" style="color: var(--link-color);">DOCKER_KUBERNETES_MIGRATION_STRATEGY.tt</a> for container network configuration, healthcheck setup, and database connectivity verification (updated Dec 20 2025).
                </p>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- IMPLEMENTATION CHECKLIST SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="implementation-checklist" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5. Implementation Checklist</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 1: Diagnostic Setup Interface (Weeks 1-3)</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>[ ] Add credentials panel to existing <code>/diagnostic/setup/debug</code> interface</li>
                <li>[ ] Database Credentials sub-panel: Edit host, port, username, password with test connection</li>
                <li>[ ] API Credentials sub-panel: Add/edit/delete for Proxmox, Cloudflare, Groq</li>
                <li>[ ] Secrets Manager sub-panel: Generate/rotate Redis password</li>
                <li>[ ] Ensure application starts even if credentials incomplete (use db_config.json or env var fallback)</li>
                <li>[ ] Test credential save/load/override cycle</li>
                <li>[ ] Document in CREDENTIALS_AUDIT_AND_PLAN.tt after each code change</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 2: Encryption (Weeks 2-4)</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>[ ] Create <code>Comserv/Util/CredentialsManager.pm</code> (external config manager, NOT in Comserv.pm)</li>
                <li>[ ] Implement AES-256 encryption (reuse ProxmoxCredentials.pm pattern)</li>
                <li>[ ] Create encrypted credential files in <code>Comserv/config/credentials/</code>: database_ency.enc, database_forager.enc, api_proxmox.enc, api_cloudflare.enc, api_groq.enc</li>
                <li>[ ] Generate encryption key on first setup or via /diagnostic/setup/debug</li>
                <li>[ ] Test key rotation mechanism</li>
                <li>[ ] Document all changes in CREDENTIALS_AUDIT_AND_PLAN.tt</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Phase 3-4: Code Refactoring (Weeks 3-6)</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>[ ] Update <code>Comserv.pm:_initialize_database_config()</code> to use CredentialsManager</li>
                <li>[ ] Update <code>DBSchemaManager.pm</code> to support CredentialsManager</li>
                <li>[ ] Test with all environments (native dev, docker dev, docker prod, K8s)</li>
                <li>[ ] Update CREDENTIALS_AUDIT_AND_PLAN.tt with code changes and integration points</li>
                <li>[ ] Update DOCKER_KUBERNETES_MIGRATION_STRATEGY.tt with container credential injection approach</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

